    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that sounds a bit optimistic tbh. a lot of these owners feel like the \"long-term benefits\" are just theoretical while the bankruptcy is real. is it actually fair to frame these regs as a \"worthwhile investment\" when they're disproportionately hitting small local shops compared to big corporations who can just absorb the costs?",
